Useful tools to automate your Debian vm:

1. generate your preseed, all the graphical install questions into a file
--> https://preseed.valete.fr/index.html

2. post online your preseed, here use raw access
--> https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Lucie-Kin/vm_installer/refs/heads/main/preseed.cfg

3. create an empty flexible image
--> qemu-img create -f qcow2 automate.qcow2 -o preallocation=off 40G

4. start your vm
--> qemu-system-x86_64 \
  -enable-kvm \
  -m 8G \
  -smp 4 \
  -cpu host \
  -net nic,model=virtio \
  -net user,hostfwd=tcp::22222-:22 \
  -drive file=/address_to_your_file/automate.qcow2,format=qcow2,if=ide \
  -cdrom /address_to_your_iso/debian-12.10.0-amd64-netinst.iso

5. locate place to share (you have to type the raw address by hand sorry)
--> https://preseed.valete.fr/about.html
--> or simply: (BIOS mode) Advanced options >> Automated install \
	>> online_preseed_address >> <Continue>

